.TH CLAUDE-SESSION-NAME 1 "2026-06-30" "agentguard" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
claude-session-name \- generate a short name for a Claude transcript
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B claude-session-name
.I transcript_path
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B claude-session-name
reads a Claude JSONL transcript, extracts recent user messages, and asks the
Claude CLI for a lowercase dash-separated session name. It is used by
AgentGuard's Claude session-end integration and can also be run manually for
transcript backfills.
.PP
System reminders and slash commands are ignored before naming. If there is no
usable transcript content or naming fails, the command exits silently.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B jq
Required to parse transcript JSON lines.
.TP
.B claude
Required to generate the name.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
A name was printed, or naming was skipped because no usable name could be
generated.
.TP
.B 1
The transcript path was missing or not a regular file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR agentguard-classify-command (1)
